<br>
You do a similiar thing for base AC on Magelo.  Go into EQ, and strip your character naked of everything (put stuff in bags or bank).  It will show you your base AC, write it down then re-equip.  Add the base AC to Magelo next time you update.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps you :) <p>Bemidien<BR>Dwarven Paladin of Brell Serilis<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=118498">Bemidien's Profile</a><BR><a href="mailto:bemidien@hotmail.com">Bemidien's Email</a><BR><a target="new" href="http://pub82.ezboard.com/btheforgottenbrotherhood">The Forgotten Brotherhood</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvaldesero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valdesero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 10:06:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Correcting ATK values in Magelo</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the help. I died in Seb last night so I was able to get the base values for my character. <br>
